  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.12.7\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nWhen running hardhat network forked from Arbitrum One, using Alchemy provider. Calling `getTransactionReceipt` fails due to the response from Alchemy failing the validation done by Hardhat. This issue appears to be limited to querying a transaction hash that is a contract deployment, in this case it appears that Alchemy omits the `to` property from the response rather than setting the property to null as the validation function expects.\r\n\r\nI was able to solve the issue for myself locally by making a modification to the validation logic [here](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/7197a6c141068e240c316f7de8486777e78c05c4/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/jsonrpc/types/output/receipt.ts#L22)\r\n\r\ncurrent: `to: nullable(rpcAddress),`\r\nchanged (and working): `to: optional(nullable(rpcAddress)),`\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n1. Hardhat config\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.4\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: \"https://arb-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/<YOUR_ALCHEMY_API_KEY>\",\r\n        blockNumber: 1250000,\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n      },\r\n      accounts: {\r\n        count: 0,\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Prepare a simple script:\r\n```\r\nimport { ethers } from \"hardhat\";\r\n\r\nconst main = async () => {\r\n     console.log(await ethers.provider.getTransactionReceipt(\"0x44a7f70cf843d696d1254ef8d359ca60fececfa2b8f5278f932735409c19c377\"));\r\n};\r\n\r\nmain().catch(error => {\r\n    console.error(error);\r\n    process.exitCode = 1;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Run local node and script:\r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat node --network hardhat\r\n...\r\nnpx hardhat run --network localhost <script.js>\r\n```\r\n4. Result:\r\n```\r\nProviderError: Invalid JSON-RPC response's result.\r\n\r\nErrors: Invalid value undefined supplied to : RpcTransactionReceipt | null/to: ADDRESS | null\r\n    at HttpProvider.request (/Users/wesleyfrederickson/repos/rnglabs/gmx-vault-contracts/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/core/providers/http.ts:88:21)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:95:5)\r\n    at async EthersProviderWrapper.send (/Users/wesleyfrederickson/repos/rnglabs/gmx-vault-contracts/node_modules/@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers/src/internal/ethers-provider-wrapper.ts:13:20)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
